   <title>Adding a JAR File Dependency</title>
   <description>TODO: Add description.</description>
   <introduction>
      <paragraph>Follow these steps to add the JAR file to your project:</paragraph>
      <ordered-list>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Download the latest release of Couchbase Lite for Android from <external-ref href="http://www.couchbase.com/download#cb-mobile">http://www.couchbase.com/download#cb-mobile</external-ref>.</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Extract the .zip file to the <strong>libs</strong> directory of your project.</paragraph>
         </list-item>
         <list-item>
            <paragraph>Modify the <strong>build.gradle</strong> file to include all jars in the <strong>libs</strong> directory:</paragraph>

            <code-block>
dependencies {
   ...
   compile fileTree(dir: 'libs', include: '*.jar')
}
</code-block>
         </list-item>
      </ordered-list>
   </introduction>
</article>
